## Why This Is Asked

This question probes the ability to design real-time 3D scene understanding from monocular video in crowded environments, focusing on dynamic occupancy rather than static poses. It tests architectural choices, data strategy, and on-device adaptation under latency constraints.

## Key Concepts

- Monocular 3D occupancy mapping in dynamic scenes
- Temporal fusion and uncertainty estimation
- On-device 5-shot adaptation for unseen objects and people
- Privacy-preserving synthetic data pipelines and domain randomization
- Edge GPU optimization and latency budgeting

## Code Example

```javascript
// Skeleton: simple occupancy loss combining BCE and temporal consistency
function occupancyLoss(logits, target, mask, prevLogits){
  // logits/target/mask shapes: [B, X, Y, Z]
  const bce = binaryCrossEntropy(logits, target, mask);
  const temporal = meanSquaredError(logits, prevLogits, mask);
  return bce + 0.1 * temporal;
}
```

## Follow-up Questions

- How would you evaluate robustness to occlusions and rapid appearance changes?
- How would you extend to multiple RGB sensors and fuse viewpoints?

## Why This Is Asked
Assesses on-device CV design, latency budgeting, and robust 3D human pose estimation for safety-critical driving.

## Key Concepts
- On-device real-time inference with a lightweight backbone
- 2D-to-3D pose reconstruction and Kalman filtering
- Self-supervised pretraining from unlabeled video
- Robustness to occlusion and adverse weather
- Quantization and latency accounting

## Code Example
```javascript
// Pseudocode for pipeline
class PedestrianPoseEstimator {
  constructor() { /* load detector, 3D head, PnP module, tracker */ }
  forward(frame) {
    const keypoints2D = this.detector.detect(frame)
    const pose3D = this.poseHead.estimate(keypoints2D)
    const pose6DoF = differentiablePnP(pose3D, this.cameraIntrinsics)
    return this.tracker.update(pose6DoF)
  }
}
```

## Follow-up Questions
- How would you extend this to multi-pedestrian tracking with identity preservation?
- What failure modes are most critical in heavy rain and how would you mitigate them?
